				<div class="th th-ddc2570 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="ddc2570" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
									<p>OTT (Over-The-Top) refers to streaming services that deliver video content directly over the internet without the need for traditional cable or satellite TV. Platforms like Netflix, Amazon Prime Video, and Disney+ are popular examples of OTT. Users can watch movies, shows, or live content anytime on smart TVs, smartphones, tablets, or laptops—completely on-demand.</p><p>CTV (Connected TV) refers to any television that connects to the internet to stream content, either through built-in smart TV features or external devices like Roku, Amazon Fire Stick, or Apple TV. CTV is a popular way people access OTT platforms. For advertisers, OTT and CTV offer targeted, trackable, and highly engaging ways to reach audiences who are no longer watching traditional TV.</p><p>CATV is a cable system that delivers TV channels and often internet and phone services to homes with better signal quality.</p>								</div>
				</div>
